  "original_title": "\u0b87.\u0baa\u0bcb.\u0b9a \u0b8a\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b86\u0bb2\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Transport Minister advises to distribute fuel to EPO employees",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Transport Minister Bandula Gunawardena has advised the Secretary of the Ministry of Transport and the Chairman of the Sri Lanka Transport Council to proceed with the operation of distributing the necessary fuel through the Sri Lanka Depot to facilitate the Sri Lanka Transport Board employees.",
        "The Minister of Transport urged the trade unions to refrain from engaging in work boycott considering the welfare of the public and the entire country would come to a standstill if the government buses were also involved in strike while private buses were limited in the public transport service.",
        "A discussion was held at the Ministry of Transport yesterday evening between the Transport Minister Bandula Gunawardena and the trade unions regarding the strike by the bus drivers and conductors of the Sri Lanka Transport Board yesterday morning demanding that they get the necessary fuel to facilitate the service.",
        "It is to be welcomed that the employees of the Sri Lanka State Bus Board have acted responsibly considering the welfare of the public despite the impact of the Covid-19 pandemic and other parts of the public transport service being involved in the boycott.",
        "We all know how much the fuel supply infrastructure in the country is in crisis. The public transport sector is suffering from fuel shortage. If the private bus service is limited and the government buses are involved in the boycott, the whole country will come to a standstill.",
        "It is possible to better understand the crisis faced by the employees while adapting to the service. I am looking forward to hold talks with the Power Minister and get at least a limited amount of fuel.",
        "Considering the dire situation the country is currently facing, I request them to engage in service instead of boycotting work for the welfare of the public.",
        "The Minister of Transport advised Kinsili Ranawaka, the Secretary of the Ministry of Transport and the Chairman of the Sri Lankan Transport Council, to carry out the operation of providing fuel to the employees through the Sri Lanka depot."
      ],
